      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">Using Corrugated Sheets for Corner and Edge Protection</h2>
      <p>Furniture and large appliances are particularly vulnerable to corner damage during handling. Sharp impacts on corners and edges can splinter wood, crack lacquered finishes, or dent metal panels. Corrugated sheets folded at 90° and taped along furniture corners create a low-cost, biodegradable corner guard. When layered two or three sheets thick, the protection is surprisingly robust.</p>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-semibold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">Combining with Other Protective Materials</h3>
      <p>For maximum protection, combine corrugated corner pads with stretch wrap film (to keep the pad in place and add surface protection) and bubble wrap on particularly vulnerable surfaces. This layered approach is standard in Malaysian furniture export packaging and significantly reduces transit damage claims compared to using any single material alone.</p>

